{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1bac62c0-a0c1-4d24-a11e-440540fdd14e","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the summary:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — no longer supported (EOL Dec 2022)\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — no longer supported (EOL May 2022)\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported (.NET Framework 4.6.2+)\n\nYou'll need to update the unsupported TFMs to at least `net6.0` (or ideally `net8.0` for current LTS).\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n1. **Package consolidation** — MSTest v3 uses a single `MSTest` package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n2. **Breaking API changes** — some deprecated v2 APIs were removed; review the [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) for details.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"193b0e00-767d-4f32-b303-6587b3d2baac","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project multi-targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3. Let me think about the compatibility issues:\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n\n1. **MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later** — `net462` should be fine (it's exactly 4.6.2).\n2. **MSTest v3 dropped support for .NET Core 3.1** — `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported. .NET Core 3.1 reached end of life in December 2022.\n\n\n3. **MSTest v3 also doesn't support .NET 5** — `net5.0` won't work either since that framework reached end of life in May 2022.\n\nMSTest v3 only supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+, .NET 6.0+, and .NET Standard 2.0, so the user would need to update both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` to at least `net6.0` or move to `net8.0` for the current LTS.\n\nBeyond the TFM issues, MSTest v3 also consolidated its packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages, and introduced some breaking API changes like altered `Assert.ThrowsException` behavior and removal of deprecated methods.","outputTokens":662,"requestId":"0C0C:14FF5F:631BBA8:6C72355:69F01F0A"},"id":"3e80047f-17fb-41da-8d70-190bc667e000","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:44:43.780Z","parentId":"8f4e931a-aa7e-4704-9176-8f80f57e38ac"}
